               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410301-name-808" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-808" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-808" type="surname" value="FORDHAM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410301-name-808" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>FRANCIS FORDHAM</persName>
                  </hi>. I am now out of business, and reside at Solomon-terrace, New-road, St. George's. The prisoner had been my porter when I was in business, and after that he lived with me to do jobs in my house, for which he had his meals—I missed various articles, and charged him with having stolen them—he said he knew nothing of them—I produced to him a handkerchief which he had pawned and sold the duplicate of—I told him if he liked to give me the things, or the duplicates, I would not give him into custody—he then said he had sold the duplicates—this box of in<lb></lb>struments was afterwards found—it is part of what I lost—the rest of the property is lost.</p>
